<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Historical Information
</head>
<p>The Continental Congress was a series of legislative bodies that convened during and after the American Revolution. As one of the original thirteen colonies, Virginia sent a delegation to the Congresses. The various sessions lead to numerous significant events and decisions such as petitions to the king, the adoption of the Declaration of Independence, as well as the establishment of the federal government.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>This series documents the expenditures of delegates representing Virginia at the Continental Congresses. Records include a ledger of expenses listing each member, as well as requests for reimbursement listing the various expenses for travel, food, lodging, and items such as coats, candles, etc..
</p>
</scopecontent>
